LEX The Invitation.

"First Person" is a person.
"Entity" is a person.
"Terms" is a text.
"Offer" is a text.
"Terms Accepted" is a binary.

The First Person appoints the Entity, and fixes the Terms.

CLAUSE: Proffer.
The First Person may send the Terms to the Entity, and afterwards register the Offer.

CLAUSE: Accept.
The Entity may declare Terms Accepted.

CLAUSE: Exchange.
The First Person may, if Terms Accepted is declared: send the Offer to the Entity.
